 on Luclin is adding to stats.  The new tinkered tradeskill booster adds 5% to your skill.  If your skill is 110 in brewing, and you hold the brewing thingy, the success check is calculated as if you have skill 115.5.  Skill advances are still calculated based on skill 110.<br>
<br>
With that in mind, and given that these are relatively low level spells, I suspect it does the same to either your spell skills or to meditation.  Either way, it would not do much for a higher level player (250 vs 260 meditate -- insignificant).  Although it might reduce fizzles for a player who has a low level for some spell skill (conjuration for the enchanter -- 180 vs 190 might help).  The way to test that this, is to give it to a lower level player who has just reached a spell level and see how the fizzle rates are.  I haven't done that test yet.<br>
<br>
I'm very disappointed to see the spells don't work in Hate and other places.  I hoped aggro management would help to counter all the enchanter-nerfs from Kunark on.  The enchanter forum on Caster's Realm lists these places where they will not work:<br>
Kedge Keep, Plane of Hate, Plane of Sky, Veeshan's Peak, Zone2, Zone6, Zone7, and Zone8<br>
<br>
I have no idea what the Zone# are.  Probably Fear.  Maybe some Luclin zones.<br>
<br>
Serius, Level 55 Enchanter to King Tearis Thex<br>
